Section section_01 (Chars 0–8420):
Section Summary: The author reflects on how Christmas has lost its magic and excitement for adults, who now have to force themselves to enjoy the holiday. In contrast, children still experience the wonder and joy of Christmas, and their enthusiasm is what helps adults to pretend to feel the same way. The author argues that Christmas was once a truly special and romantic day, but now it has become a time of gluttony, expensiveness, and obligation. The fact that adults have to deliberately induce the "Christmas feeling" suggests that the holiday has lost its genuine significance and heartiness. The author believes that acknowledging this decline is the first step towards understanding and addressing the problem, rather than simply denying or ignoring it.
